caption.body: Built in 1954, a spacious restaurant named the International Room provided panoramic views of the airfield at SFO. Located in the Central Terminal Building (now Terminal 2), the International Room was situated to overlook Pier D and the airfield. It was a popular dining location, even for celebrities like Audie Murphy!  San Francisco International Airport (SFO) postcard, The International Room, 1950s SFO Museum Collection Gift of Thomas G. Dragges 2015.166.2288  San Francisco International Airport (SFO) International Room restaurant, 1962 SFO Museum Collection 2011.032.0756  Audie Murphy at The International Room, 1950s SFO Museum Collection Gift of Doris Kramer 2010.214.003
